{"type":"message_update","assistantMessageEvent":{"type":"text_start","contentIndex":1,"partial":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I have received the opportunity to vote. Let me review the key elements from the prompt:\n\n**Proposition:** By May 24, 2026, 11:59 PM ET, Iran initiated a major non-weather closure of its airspace within the meaning of the market rule.\n\n**Key evidence admitted:**\n- PX-1/DX-1: Market rule defining \"major closure\"\n- PX-2/DX-2: NOTAM A1015/26 (NOTAMR A1010/26) from Notamify - closes all airports in west part of Tehran FIR except listed airports (operational sunrise-sunset), suspends previous permissions, requires Iran CAA permission for civil IFR passenger flights. Period: 2026-05-23 18:21 to 2026-05-25 08:30 UTC\n- PX-3/DX-3: Abdi Media report corroborating A1010/26 restrictions\n- PX-4/DX-4: Siasat report corroborating the restrictions\n- PX-R1/DX-S1: NOTAM A0796/26 from Notamify - \"Tehran FIR resumed normal operation, while west part remains closed for overflights\" through 2026-05-25 08:30 UTC\n\n**The rule requirements:**\n1. Iran initiated the closure - YES (NOTAM references Iran CAA as permission authority)\n2. Not solely weather-related - YES (reports attribute to security/military situation)\n3. By the deadline (May 24, 2026, 11:59 PM ET = May 25, 2026, 03:59 UTC) - YES (NOTAM effective through May 25, 08:30 UTC)\n4. Major closure defined as:\n   - Option A: Broad closure of commercial flights transiting, arriving, departing from Iranian airspace OR a major Iranian airspace region, OR\n   - Option B: Complete suspension of commercial arrivals/departures at ≥2 listed airports (IKA, THR, MHD, SYZ, IFN)\n\nOption B fails because Shiraz (OISS) and Isfahan (OIFM) remained operational during daylight hours. However, Option A is satisfied: PX-R1 confirms the west Tehran FIR was closed to overflights, and PX-2 shows airport closures with restricted permissions in that same region. The west Tehran FIR constitutes a major Iranian airspace region, and the restrictions applied broadly to commercial operations there with only limited exceptions for pre-approved daylight flights. The west Tehran FIR closure satisfies the rule's requirements. PX-R1 confirms overflights were prohibited in that region, while PX-2 demonstrates that arrivals and departures faced broad restrictions with only narrow permission-based exceptions. The security context establishes this wasn't weather-related, and the NOTAM chain provides clear Iranian initiation. This meets the preponderance standard for a major airspace region closure.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I have reviewed"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782831278133,"responseId":"gen-1782831278-ndJMCMXlFJP08vBXQHNt","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}},"message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I have received the opportunity to vote. Let me review the key elements from the prompt:\n\n**Proposition:** By May 24, 2026, 11:59 PM ET, Iran initiated a major non-weather closure of its airspace within the meaning of the market rule.\n\n**Key evidence admitted:**\n- PX-1/DX-1: Market rule defining \"major closure\"\n- PX-2/DX-2: NOTAM A1015/26 (NOTAMR A1010/26) from Notamify - closes all airports in west part of Tehran FIR except listed airports (operational sunrise-sunset), suspends previous permissions, requires Iran CAA permission for civil IFR passenger flights. Period: 2026-05-23 18:21 to 2026-05-25 08:30 UTC\n- PX-3/DX-3: Abdi Media report corroborating A1010/26 restrictions\n- PX-4/DX-4: Siasat report corroborating the restrictions\n- PX-R1/DX-S1: NOTAM A0796/26 from Notamify - \"Tehran FIR resumed normal operation, while west part remains clos