loses-its-airspace-by-may-24\nCaptured API file: source-captures/polymarket-gamma-event.json\nCaptured May 24 API file: source-captures/polymarket-gamma-market-may-24.json\nCaptured event page file: source-captures/polymarket-page-and-api-extract.txt\nCaptured May 24 page file or error: source-captures/polymarket-gamma-market-may-24.json\nCapture time: 2026-05-24T01:44:04Z\n\n## Event\n\n- event id: 438327\n- ticker/slug: iran-closes-its-airspace-by / iran-closes-its-airspace-by\n- title: Iran closes its airspace by...?\n- event createdAt: 2026-05-01T16:11:36.585944Z\n- event creationDate: 2026-05-01T18:22:49.431549Z\n- event startDate: 2026-05-01T18:22:49.431559Z\n- event endDate: 2026-05-31T00:00:00Z\n- event active: True\n- event closed: False\n- event volume at capture: 34658537.51144401\n\n## May 24 market\n\n- market id: 2241873\n- slug: iran-closes-its-airspace-by-may-24\n- question: Iran closes its airspace by May 24?\n- groupItemTitle: May 24\n- conditionId: 0x4ba348328e4d4ddee9e6734c9a369b2e8138611651f9f6dc8f59dea51df6c734\n- questionID: 0x30ebd10971cc044380ce6495e791828e9e0291fbb48550ca8be42149e1982791\n- createdAt: 2026-05-12T15:03:45.641355Z\n- startDate: 2026-05-12T15:08:30.267422Z\n- endDate: 2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\n- endDateIso: 2026-05-24\n- active: True\n- closed: False\n- acceptingOrders: True\n- umaResolutionStatus: disputed\n- umaResolutionStatuses: [\"proposed\", \"disputed\", \"proposed\", \"disputed\"]\n- outcomes: [\"Yes\", \"No\"]\n- outcomePrices: [\"0.157\", \"0.843\"]\n- lastTradePrice: 0.16\n- bestBid/bestAsk: 0.15 / 0.164\n- updatedAt: 2026-05-24T01:35:13.748834Z\n- volume at capture: 8289170.735521075\n\n## Rule text\n\nThis market will resolve to “Yes” if Iran initiates a major closure of its airspace, that is not solely due to weather conditions, by the listed date, 11:59 PM ET. Otherwise, this market will resolve to “No”.\n\nA “major closure” is defined as a broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian Airspace region. A qualifying closure must apply generally to flights across Iran or a major Iranian airspace region. Limited cancellations, delays, or other partial closures will not qualify. Limited exceptions to a broad closure, however, will not disqualify such a closure from counting (e.g. exceptions for certain flights pre-approved by the Iranian Civil Aviation Authority may be permitted).\n\nAny non-weather complete suspension of commercial arrivals and departures affecting at least two of the following airports will qualify: Imam Khomeini International Airport (IKA), Mehrabad Airport (THR), Mashhad International Airport (MHD), Shiraz International Airport (SYZ), or Isfahan International Airport (IFN).\n\nQualifying previous examples include the January 2026 total closure of Iranian airspace except to international flights with express governmental permission (https://www.reuters.com/world/middle-east/iran-shuts-airspace-most-flights-flightradar24-says-2026-01-14/) and the April 2024 closure of Iran’s western airspace (https://www.reuters.com/world/middle-east/iranian-airports-cancel-flights-until-monday-morning-2024-04-14/). Non-qualifying examples include the January 27, 2026 partial closure of Iranian airspace around the Strait of Hormuz (https://www.aa.com.tr/en/middle-east/iran-issues-airspace-notice-for-military-drills-near-strait-of-hormuz/3812508) and the January 25 - April 25, 2026 VFR (Visual Flight Rules) flights suspension which did not broadly close commercial aviation in a qualifying region (https://www.intellinews.com/iran-suspends-general-aviation-and-vfr-flights-in-new-airspace-directive-421997/).\n\nWarnings, No-Fly-Zones, or other flight restrictions imposed by airlines or countries other than Iran will not be sufficient for a “Yes” resolution.\n\nAirspace closures which occur solely due to weather conditions will not qualify.\n\nThe primary resolution sources for this market will be official information from Iranian aviation authorities and a consensus of credible reporting.\n\n## Notes for arbitration\n\nThe proposition tracks the rule text, not the platform-resolution question. The operative elements are: (1) Iran initiated the closure; (2) the closure was not solely weather-related; (3) the closure occurred by May 24, 2026, 11:59 PM ET; (4) the closure was a major closure, defined by the rule as a broad closure, cancellation, or suspension of commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from Iranian airspace or a major Iranian airspace region; or a non-weather complete suspension of commercial arrivals and departures affecting at least two listed airports; and (5) the primary sources are official information from Iranian aviation authorities and a consensus of credible reporting.\n\n\nSubmitted evidence:\n[plaintiff arguments] Notamify capture of OIIX A1015/26 replacing A1010/26 (ev_263eb57c30ed_submitted-evidence-01-plaintiff-263eb57c30ed)\nSource: https://notamify.com/notams/OIIX/67435351-52f9-4d17-8f4c-497a21dd94bf\nSHA-256: `263eb57c30edcfb2a5af3c4e0b4e4f9d4ddaf771b5506ad7ada78c95f3f36768`\nBytes: 1612\nRelevance: Shows raw NOTAM text for Tehran FIR/OIIX stating A1015/26 NOTAMR A1010/26, applicable May 23 18:21 UTC to May 25 08:30 UTC, closing all airports in the west part of Tehran FIR except listed airports, limiting them to sunrise-sunset operations, suspending previous permissions, and requiring Iran CAA permission for civil IFR passenger flights.\n\n[plaintiff arguments] Abdi Media report on A1010/26 western Tehran FIR restrictions (ev_4a64799d1143_submitted-evidence-02-plaintiff-4a64799d1143)\nSource: https://abdimedia.net/en/economic/notam\nSHA-256: `4a64799d1143749a7fd6731707c35c9fcf7ef354a9059082ac2e05de7ee07d64`\nBytes: 1483\nRelevance: Corroborates A1010/26 details: restrictions and closure of airports in western Iran/Tehran FIR extended until May 25, 2026; all airports in western Tehran FIR closed except specified airports with limited sunrise-sunset operations; prior permissions canceled and new Civil Aviation Organization authorization required for IFR passenger flights.\n\n[plaintiff arguments] Siasat report on Iran western airspace restrictions and OIIX A1010/26 (ev_05dfc9131a91_submitted-evidence-03-plaintiff-05dfc9131a91)\nSource: https://www.siasat.com/trump-considers-new-iran-strikes-as-diplomacy-enters-critical-phase-3475705/\nSHA-256: `05dfc9131a911776684c40720c6825a2ef69f6a6d377f14950e0506c8465e378`\nBytes: 1238\nRelevance: Provides independent corroborating reporting that a NOTAM identified as OIIX A1010/26 announced closure of airports across the western section of the Tehran FIR, limited operations to daylight, and required fresh Iran CAA approval before passenger flights in affected areas.\n\n[plaintiff rebuttals] Notamify capture of OIIX A0796/26 west Tehran FIR overflight closure (ev_682e9dcc5947_submitted-evidence-04-plaintiff-682e9dcc5947)\nSource: https://notamify.com/notams/OIIX/4ec67845-38c8-470a-b7cb-e32ce5f266c4\nSHA-256: `682e9dcc59479189306395e48f8103206308ca5d42b8c28cc591f3f69252d966`\nBytes: 1964\nRelevance: Directly addresses the defense argument that plaintiff lacked evidence about transiting/overflights. A0796/26 states Tehran FIR resumed normal operation while the west part remained closed for overflights, with applicability through May 25 08:30 UTC; A1015/26 expressly references A0796/26.\n\nTechnical reports:\n[plaintiff] Source-chain and timing analysis\nThe May 24 11:59 PM ET deadline converts to 2026-05-25 03:59 UTC. The submitted Notamify raw NOTAM capture shows OIIX A1015/26, replacing A1010/26, effective 2026-05-23 18:21 UTC to 2026-05-25 08:30 UTC, so it covers the deadline. It identifies a western Tehran FIR airport closure with listed daylight-only exceptions, suspension of prior permissions, and new Iran CAA permission required for civil IFR passenger flights. The corroborating reports describe the same A1010/26 restriction as an Iran CAA/Civil Aviation Organization action and place it in security/military, not weather, context. Remaining limitation: the raw text is from a NOTAM repository rather than a direct official CAA archive, so weight rests on consistency between raw repository text and independent reports.\n\n[defendant] Defense source-chain and adverse-search ledger\nFor the defendant argument I inspected the visible record and read all three new plaintiff evidence files. I searched exact NOTAM identifiers and phrases: A1015/26 A1010/26 OIIX, ALL AIRPORTS IN WEST PART OF TEHRAN FIR, and A0796/26 TEHRAN FIR. The search located the same Notamify A1015/26 capture, a Notamify A0796/26 lead indicating Tehran FIR had resumed normal operation while the west part remained closed for overflights and the east was open subject to conditions, and related east/west airport-operation NOTAM leads. No official CAA.IRI archive was found in the quick search. The adverse A0796 lead partly supports plaintiff, so I did not submit it as defense evidence; the defense argument instead focuses on the admitted text’s source-chain and rule-fit limits.\n\n[plaintiff] Targeted rebuttal source check\nDefendant argued plaintiff lacked evidence that the restriction affected transiting/overflights. A targeted search for A0796/26, the NOTAM referenced in PX-2/A1015, found a Notamify raw NOTAM capture stating that Tehran FIR resumed normal operation while the west part remained closed for overflights, effective through 2026-05-25 08:30 UTC. This was submitted as PX-R1. It directly complements PX-2, which covers western Tehran FIR airport closures, daylight-only exceptions, suspended permissions, and new Iran CAA approval for civil IFR passenger flights.\n\nCall submit_council_vote with vote=demonstrated or vote=not_demonstrated.\nKeep the rationale brief: no more than three sentences.\n\nCouncil API instructions:\nYou are a council member. Decide the proposition from the admitted record.\nYou may examine admitted evidence through read-only tools when exact bytes, metadata, or exhibit contents matter.\nDo not search the web, introduce new facts, create new evidence, or upload evidence.\nWhen ready, call submit_council_vote exactly once with vote=demonstrated or vote=not_demonstrated and a concise rationale.\n","state":"ready","status":"ready","tools":[{"description":"Return the current visible arbitration record for this council member.","input_schema":{"additionalProperties":false,"properties":{},"type":"object"},"name":"get_case","read_only":true},{"description":"List visible immutable record evidence.","input_schema":{"additionalProperties":false,"properties":{},"type":"object"},"name":"list_evidence","read_only":true},{"description":"Return metadata and read limits for one visible evidence item.","input_schema":{"additionalProperties":false,"properties":{"evidence_id":{"type":"string"}},"required":["evidence_id"],"type":"object"},"name":"stat_evidence","read_only":true},{"description":"Read a bounded byte range from one visible evidence item as base64.","input_schema":{"additionalProperties":false,"properties":{"evidence_id":{"type":"string"},"length":{"minimum":1,"type":"integer"},"offset":{"minimum":0,"type":"integer"}},"required":["evidence_id","offset","length"],"type":"object"},"name":"read_evidence_range","read_only":true},{"description":"Submit one council vote for the current deliberation opportunity.","input_schema":{"additionalProperties":false,"properties":{"rationale":{"type":"string"},"vote":{"enum":["demonstrated","not_demonstrated"],"type":"string"}},"required":["vote","rationale"],"type":"object"},"name":"submit_council_vote","read_only":false}],"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":false,"deadline":"2026-06-30T15:09:25.989494614Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C1","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C1","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":887868,"role_id":"council","turn_number":9},"wait":{"reason":"ready","state_version":13,"version":13}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"wait_for_opportunity"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782831278127},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I have received the opportunity to vote. Let me review the key elements from the prompt:\n\n**Proposition:** By May 24, 2026, 11:59 PM ET, Iran initiated a major non-weather closure of its airspace within the meaning of the market rule.\n\n**Key evidence admitted:**\n- PX-1/DX-1: Market rule defining \"major closure\"\n- PX-2/DX-2: NOTAM A1015/26 (NOTAMR A1010/26) from Notamify - closes all airports in west part of Tehran FIR except listed airports (operational sunrise-sunset), suspends previous permissions, requires Iran CAA permission for civil IFR passenger flights. Period: 2026-05-23 18:21 to 2026-05-25 08:30 UTC\n- PX-3/DX-3: Abdi Media report corroborating A1010/26 restrictions\n- PX-4/DX-4: Siasat report corroborating the restrictions\n- PX-R1/DX-S1: NOTAM A0796/26 from Notamify - \"Tehran FIR resumed normal operation, while west part remains closed for overflights\" through 2026-05-25 08:30 UTC\n\n**The rule requirements:**\n1. Iran initiated the closure - YES (NOTAM references Iran CAA as permission authority)\n2. Not solely weather-related - YES (reports attribute to security/military situation)\n3. By the deadline (May 24, 2026, 11:59 PM ET = May 25, 2026, 03:59 UTC) - YES (NOTAM effective through May 25, 08:30 UTC)\n4. Major closure defined as:\n   - Option A: Broad closure of commercial flights transiting, arriving, departing from Iranian airspace OR a major Iranian airspace region, OR\n   - Option B: Complete suspension of commercial arrivals/departures at ≥2 listed airports (IKA, THR, MHD, SYZ, IFN)\n\nOption B fails because Shiraz (OISS) and Isfahan (OIFM) remained operational during daylight hours. However, Option A is satisfied: PX-R1 confirms the west Tehran FIR was closed to overflights, and PX-2 shows airport closures with restricted permissions in that same region. The west Tehran FIR constitutes a major Iranian airspace region, and the restrictions applied broadly to commercial operations there with only limited exceptions for pre-approved daylight flights. The west Tehran FIR closure satisfies the rule's requirements. PX-R1 confirms overflights were prohibited in that region, while PX-2 demonstrates that arrivals and departures faced broad restrictions with only narrow permission-based exceptions. The security context establishes this wasn't weather-related, and the NOTAM chain provides clear Iranian initiation. This meets the preponderance standard for a major airspace region closure.","thinkingSignature":"reasoning"},{"type":"text","text":"I have reviewed the arbitration record and admitted evidence. Let me analyze the key elements:\n\n**Proposition:** By May 24, 2026, 11:59 PM ET, Iran initiated a major non-weather closure of its airspace within the meaning of the market rule.\n\n**Key findings from admitted evidence:**\n\n1. **Iran initiation:** PX-2 (NOTAM A1015/26) requires new permission from Iran CAA for civil IFR passenger flights, establishing Iranian authority initiated the restriction.\n\n2. **Non-weather cause:** PX-3 and PX-4 attribute the restrictions to security/military situation, not weather.\n\n3. **Timing:** The NOTAMs are effective through 2026-05-25 08:30 UTC, which covers the deadline (May 24, 11:59 PM ET = May 25, 03:59 UTC).\n\n4. **Major closure:** The rule has two paths:\n   - **Airport path (Option B):** Requires complete suspension at ≥2 listed airports. This fails—PX-2 shows Shiraz (OISS) and Isfahan (OIFM) remained operational daylight hours with permission.\n   - **Major region path (Option A):** PX-R1 (A0796/26) shows west Tehran FIR \"closed for overflights\" (transiting). PX-2 shows airports in west Tehran FIR closed except limited daylight/permission exceptions (arrivals/departures). Western Tehran FIR qualifies as a major Iranian airspace region, and the rule expressly states limited exceptions do not disqualify a broad closure.\n\nThe preponderance of admitted evidence supports that Iran initiated a major non-weather closure affecting commercial flights transiting, arriving in, and departing from a major Iranian airspace region (western Tehran FIR).\n\n"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_c4d89b0b1a4546f586501c46","name":"mcp","arguments":{"tool":"aar_submit_council_vote","args":"{\"vote\":\"demonstrated\",\"rationale\":\"The admitted NOTAMs A0796/26 (PX-R1) and A1015/26 (PX-2) establish that by the May 24, 2026 deadline, Iran CAA closed western Tehran FIR—a major Iranian airspace region—to overflights while restricting airport arrivals/departures to limited daylight operations requiring new Iran CAA permission. The record proves Iran initiation, non-weather security causation (PX-3, PX-4), and timing, satisfying the rule's major-region closure path under a preponderance standard.\"}"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":20542,"output":1227,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21769,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1782831278133,"responseId":"gen-1782831278-ndJMCMXlFJP08vBXQHNt","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"},{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_c4d89b0b1a4546f586501c46","toolName":"mcp","content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C1\ncase_id: arb-ex11a-20260630143613\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C1\nremaining_ms: 861054\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex11a-20260630143613\",\"member_id\":\"C1\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T15:09:25.989494614Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C1\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C1\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":861054,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":9}}"}],"details":{"mode":"call","mcpResult":{"content":[{"type":"text","text":"ok: true\nmember_id: C1\ncase_id: arb-ex11a-20260630143613\nphase: deliberation\nopportunity_id: deliberation:1:C1\nremaining_ms: 861054\nattempts_remaining: 3\njson: {\"case_id\":\"arb-ex11a-20260630143613\",\"member_id\":\"C1\",\"ok\":true,\"result\":{\"text\":\"Council vote accepted.\"},\"turn\":{\"attempts_max\":3,\"attempts_remaining\":3,\"completed\":true,\"deadline\":\"2026-06-30T15:09:25.989494614Z\",\"deliberation_round\":1,\"member_id\":\"C1\",\"opportunity_id\":\"deliberation:1:C1\",\"phase\":\"deliberation\",\"remaining_ms\":861054,\"role_id\":\"council\",\"turn_number\":9}}"}],"structuredContent":{"case_id":"arb-ex11a-20260630143613","member_id":"C1","ok":true,"result":{"text":"Council vote accepted."},"turn":{"attempts_max":3,"attempts_remaining":3,"completed":true,"deadline":"2026-06-30T15:09:25.989494614Z","deliberation_round":1,"member_id":"C1","opportunity_id":"deliberation:1:C1","phase":"deliberation","remaining_ms":861054,"role_id":"council","turn_number":9}},"isError":false},"server":"aar","tool":"submit_council_vote"},"isError":false,"timestamp":1782831304937},{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"My vote was accepted. The council vote for case arb-ex11a-20260630143613 has been submitted successfully with vote \"demonstrated\" - finding that the proposition was proven by a preponderance of the admitted evidence."}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"openrouter","model":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-02-15","usage":{"input":21345,"output":63,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":21408,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1782831304938,"responseId":"gen-1782831305-xuFYzz3mrraTQzYvDpcO","responseModel":"qwen/qwen3.5-plus-20260216"}],"willRetry":false}
